      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CINQUE STELLE (7) jumped a $1.30 favourite at the end of last campaign and wasn't disgraced in a CL1 at this track and trip before the spell. Her recent trial was impressive and Pike was on board for that heat. Continues to show talent and she can return with a bang. SILENT DIVA (2) was just fair before the break, though her recent trial coming into this showed she is back on song. Fiore taking the ride on resumption is a key booking and the wide alley is no issue on resumption. Can resume on a positive note. ADMIRE THE GIRL (4) was first-up after a long break at Northam where she showed she's still capable. She'll be better for that run and CJP hops on board now. Still has some upside and she can put her best foot forward. NEW TARGET (3) pulled up with an issue last time out but can bounce back third-up into the campaign. SESH (8) is racing well and won't be far away.",
